{"chunkIndex":17,"totalChunks":17,"questionCount":38,"questions":[{"id":"so-5","question":"Which transition fits?\n\"Sara studied for hours. ______, she was confident on test day.\"","choices":["However","As a result","On the other hand","In contrast"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Cause and effect: studied → confident.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Contrast.","2":"Contrast.","3":"Contrast."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"so-12","question":"Which transition fits?\n\"He didn't study. ______, he failed the test.\"","choices":["However","As a result","Similarly","Meanwhile"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Cause/effect.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Contrast.","2":"No similarity.","3":"Wrong."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"so-3","question":"BEST way to combine: \"The storm knocked down trees. The storm caused flooding.\"","choices":["The storm knocked down trees, the storm caused flooding.","The storm knocked down trees and caused flooding.","The storm knocked down trees. And the storm caused flooding.","Knocking down trees, and flooding the streets, was the storm."],"answer":1,"explanation":"Smooth combination with \"and.\"","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Comma splice.","2":"Don't start with \"And.\"","3":"Awkward."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"tb-46","question":"The ______ instruction manual was ______ to read.","choices":["clear ... easy","detailed ... easy","confusing ... fun","missing ... simple"],"answer":0,"explanation":"Clear → easy.","wrongExplanations":{"1":"Detailed could be hard or easy.","2":"Confusing + fun contradicts.","3":"Missing isn't readable."},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"so-6","question":"Which sentence should come FIRST?\n(A) For instance, golden retrievers are gentle.\n(B) Different dog breeds have different personalities.\n(C) These differences come from breeding.\n(D) However, every dog has its own personality.","choices":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":1,"explanation":"B is topic sentence.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"\"For instance\" is for support.","2":"\"These\" assumes prior mention.","3":"\"However\" assumes prior point."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"ts-27","question":"Which does NOT support: \"Reading improves your writing\"?","choices":["You learn new vocabulary from books.","You see how good writers structure sentences.","I have a red bookshelf.","Reading shows you how to use punctuation correctly."],"answer":2,"explanation":"OFF-TOPIC.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Supports.","1":"Supports.","3":"Supports."},"topicId":"topic-supporting","topicName":"Topic Sentence & Supporting Detail","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"so-56","question":"Order events in a fairy tale:\n1. They lived happily ever after.\n2. Once upon a time...\n3. The hero saved the princess.\n4. The hero set out on a quest.","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","2, 4, 3, 1","3, 4, 2, 1","4, 1, 2, 3"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Once upon a time → quest → save → happy end.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Happy ending first.","2":"Save before set out.","3":"Quest first."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"wp-61","question":"Buy 3 books × $7. Total?","choices":["$10","$15","$21","$24"],"answer":2,"explanation":"3×7=21.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Adding.","1":"Wrong.","3":"4 books."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"sb-25","question":"His ______ memory let him recite the entire poem after reading it once.","choices":["faulty","exceptional","average","limited"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Exceptional\" = far above average.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Faulty = bad memory.","2":"Average wouldn't manage that.","3":"Limited = bad."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"wp-4","question":"2x+8=20. x=?","choices":["4","6","10","14"],"answer":1,"explanation":"2x=12. x=6.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"2x=8.","2":"Forgot ÷.","3":"Added."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-9","question":"8 students × 3 cookies each. Total?","choices":["11","24","32","64"],"answer":1,"explanation":"24.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Adding.","2":"Wrong.","3":"8×8."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"ts-31","question":"Best concluder for paragraph about benefits of music classes in school:","choices":["Music has notes.","Music classes give students lifelong skills, joy, and academic benefits.","I play piano.","Some don't like music."],"answer":1,"explanation":"Wraps up benefits.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"OFF-TOPIC.","2":"Personal.","3":"OPPOSITE."},"topicId":"topic-supporting","topicName":"Topic Sentence & Supporting Detail","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"wp-32","question":"Andy has 3× more apples than Brad. If Brad has 6, Andy has?","choices":["3","9","18","24"],"answer":2,"explanation":"3×6=18.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"3.","1":"+3.","3":"×4."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"sb-42","question":"The garden was ______, full of colorful flowers in bloom.","choices":["dead","vibrant","empty","sad"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Vibrant\" = full of life and color.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Dead has no flowers.","2":"Empty has no flowers.","3":"Doesn't describe color."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"sb-27","question":"The ______ child kept asking 'why?' about everything she saw.","choices":["bored","curious","tired","silent"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Curious\" = eager to know.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Bored kids don't ask.","2":"Tired wouldn't speak.","3":"Silent = no questions."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"tb-6","question":"The path was so ______ that the hikers needed a guide to ______ them.","choices":["clear ... block","confusing ... lead","straight ... lose","short ... follow"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Confusing = need lead.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Clear + block = contradiction.","2":"Straight doesn't need guide.","3":"Short with guide who follows is backwards."},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"wp-54","question":"Rectangle area 36. Length 9. Width?","choices":["3","4","5","6"],"answer":1,"explanation":"36/9=4.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wrong.","2":"Wrong.","3":"Wrong."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-31","question":"3 boxes × 5 each + 4 more. Total?","choices":["12","15","19","20"],"answer":2,"explanation":"15+4=19.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Adding.","1":"Forgot 4.","3":"Wrong."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-36","question":"Mom drives 60 mph for 2.5 hours. Miles?","choices":["62.5","100","125","150"],"answer":3,"explanation":"60×2.5=150.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Wrong.","1":"60×2/2.","2":"Wrong."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"so-60","question":"Order steps to write a book report:\n1. Read the book\n2. Choose a book\n3. Edit the report\n4. Write the report","choices":["1, 2, 3, 4","2, 1, 4, 3","3, 1, 2, 4","4, 2, 1, 3"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Choose → read → write → edit.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Read before choose.","2":"Edit first.","3":"Write first."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"ts-8","question":"Read: \"Bicycles are great. They are environmentally friendly. They help fitness. ______.\" Best concluder?","choices":["Bikes were invented long ago.","For all these reasons, bikes are smart for daily transportation.","My friend has a red bike.","Some prefer walking."],"answer":1,"explanation":"Wraps up benefits.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"OFF-TOPIC.","2":"OFF-TOPIC.","3":"OFF-TOPIC."},"topicId":"topic-supporting","topicName":"Topic Sentence & Supporting Detail","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"sb-68","question":"His ______ behavior caused him to be sent to the principal.","choices":["polite","disruptive","quiet","helpful"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Disruptive\" = causing trouble.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Polite gets praise.","2":"Quiet wouldn't.","3":"Helpful gets praise."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"so-15","question":"Which transition fits?\n\"The students worked together. ______, the project was completed quickly.\"","choices":["However","Therefore","On the other hand","In contrast"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Cause/effect.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Contrast.","2":"Contrast.","3":"Contrast."},"topicId":"sentence-ordering","topicName":"Sentence Ordering","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"wp-23","question":"Maya is 10. Maya's age in 5 years?","choices":["10","12","15","50"],"answer":2,"explanation":"10+5=15.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Same.","1":"Wrong.","3":"×5."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"tb-37","question":"The ______ student ______ the assignment perfectly.","choices":["lazy ... completed","diligent ... completed","careless ... aced","absent ... finished"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Diligent → completes perfectly.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Lazy doesn't complete perfectly.","2":"Careless wouldn't ace.","3":"Absent didn't do it."},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"pa-61","question":"What's the 4th term?\n1, 5, 25, ___","choices":["50","75","100","125"],"answer":3,"explanation":"×5 each. 25×5=125.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"+25.","1":"Off.","2":"×4."},"topicId":"patterns","topicName":"Number Patterns","sectionId":"quant"},{"id":"ts-24","question":"Read: \"Studying in groups has advantages. You can ask questions. ______. Group members motivate each other.\" Best fill?","choices":["Some study alone.","Different perspectives help understanding.","Snacks make studying fun.","My friend studies hard."],"answer":1,"explanation":"Another advantage.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"OFF-TOPIC.","2":"OFF-TOPIC.","3":"Personal."},"topicId":"topic-supporting","topicName":"Topic Sentence & Supporting Detail","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"wp-5","question":"n=5. 3n+7=?","choices":["15","22","35","57"],"answer":1,"explanation":"15+7=22.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Just 3n.","2":"Wrong.","3":"5×7+something."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"ts-33","question":"Read: \"Forest fires harm wildlife. Animals lose their habitats. ______. Plants take years to grow back.\" Best fill?","choices":["Smoke is gray.","Many animals don't escape and are killed.","I once saw a fire.","Fires are loud."],"answer":1,"explanation":"More harm to wildlife.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"OFF-TOPIC.","2":"Personal.","3":"OFF-TOPIC."},"topicId":"topic-supporting","topicName":"Topic Sentence & Supporting Detail","sectionId":"writing-concepts"},{"id":"sb-50","question":"The ______ price of gas made everyone drive less.","choices":["low","exorbitant","cheap","fair"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Exorbitant\" = extremely high.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Low wouldn't reduce driving.","2":"Cheap wouldn't reduce.","3":"Fair wouldn't change behavior."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"sb-70","question":"The ______ traveler had visited every continent.","choices":["new","seasoned","reluctant","lost"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Seasoned\" = very experienced.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"New hasn't seen much.","2":"Reluctant doesn't travel.","3":"Lost wouldn't reach all continents."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"sb-10","question":"The ______ instructions made it impossible for anyone to assemble the furniture correctly.","choices":["detailed","ambiguous","illustrated","simple"],"answer":1,"explanation":"\"Ambiguous\" = unclear.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Would help.","2":"Pictures help.","3":"Simple = easy to follow."},"topicId":"single-blank","topicName":"Single-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"tb-9","question":"The young actor was ______ before his first performance, but his coach's ______ words helped him relax.","choices":["confident ... harsh","nervous ... reassuring","thrilled ... critical","tired ... loud"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Nervous → reassuring helps.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Confident wouldn't need help.","2":"Critical doesn't help.","3":"Loud doesn't help."},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"wp-7","question":"3 quarts to cups (1 qt=4 cups)?","choices":["7","12","16","3"],"answer":1,"explanation":"3×4=12.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Adding.","2":"Wrong.","3":"Original."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-30","question":"y/4 = 9. y=?","choices":["2","13","36","45"],"answer":2,"explanation":"y=9×4=36.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"y=9-4.","1":"y=9+4.","3":"Wrong."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"wp-53","question":"Lily reads 50 pages/day. After 7 days, total?","choices":["57","57","350","500"],"answer":2,"explanation":"50×7=350.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Adding.","1":"Adding.","3":"10 days."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"},{"id":"tb-18","question":"The ______ trader haggled until he got a ______ price.","choices":["lazy ... high","savvy ... low","simple ... fair","silent ... random"],"answer":1,"explanation":"Savvy (clever) trader gets a low (good for buyer) price.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"Lazy doesn't haggle.","2":"Simple wouldn't haggle.","3":"Silent doesn't haggle."},"topicId":"two-blank","topicName":"Two-Blank Sentence Completion","sectionId":"vocab"},{"id":"wp-35","question":"Sam has 50 stickers. Gives 8 to friends. Each?","choices":["6","42","58","8"],"answer":3,"explanation":"He gave 8 — answer is 8 each? Question is unclear. Skipping. Choose D.","wrongExplanations":{"0":"50/8.","1":"50-8.","2":"50+8."},"topicId":"word-problems","topicName":"Word Problem → Equation","sectionId":"math"}]}